LANG
====
   do-while

DESCRIPTION
===========
      KEYWORD
      =======
      DESCRIPTION
      ===========
      SYNTAX
      ======
      DESCRIPTION
      ===========
   Execute 'statment' until 'expr' evaulates to 0.

   A 'break' in the 'statement' will terminate the loop. A 'continue' will 
   continue the execution from the beginning of the loop.

SEE ALSO
========
   `for`, `foreach`, `while`, `if`, `switch`
